PRELIMINARY REMARK: The using rules of the software MEFISTO

The using of the software Mefisto and its numerical results are FREE.
But, it is forbidden to trade the software without an agreement with the authors
who can be contacted by e-mail at perronnet@ann.jussieu.fr

More, any publication must mention the using of the software MEFISTO and
its access on the web at https://www.ljll.math.upmc.fr/perronnet/mefisto.gene.html

The RIGHT BEHAVIOUR of the software is NEVER GUARANTED.
Any damage, done by the using of the software, could never be the subject of
compensation.

Any try of installation implies that the User has accepted implictly this rules.
*******************************************************************************


Prerequisites on HARDWARE and SOFTWARE:
=======================================
The installation needs of 
- a PC under system LINUX or equivalent;
- a main memory of 1 giga-bytes;
- a disk memory of 1 giga-bytes to store the software and execution files;
- the libraries X11-WINDOW SYSTEM;
- a graphic card which permits under X11 a definition of the display
  1024x768 or 1280x1024 or +  with mode PseudoColor (256 colors) or TrueColor.


DOWNLOAD and INSTALL the SOURCE of MEFISTO
==========================================
Let DirMefisto (as $HOME) the directory which will receive the file mefistosource.tgz
This directory name is now refered DirMefisto
- Give it the write access right by
  chmod 777 DirMefisto
- With a navigator as Mozilla or Firefox or ... , go to the URL
  https://www.ljll.math.upmc.fr/perronnet/instalsource.php
- Download in DirMefisto the 2 files: 
  . instalsource.bash
  . mefistosource.tgz
- go to this directory with the command
  cd DirMefisto
- Type ./instalsource.bash   under bash and follow the statements... (language,...)
  Wait patiently because many subroutines are compiled and the binding is long...
- Give the access rights to DirMefisto
  chmod -R 755 DirMefisto

At the installation level, a problem may be:
- a no correct name (upper case, ...)
- a DirMefisto name with a blank character
- a not possible access to DirMefisto by incorrect access rights
- a not installed gcc compiler or gfortran (load it)
- a not installed X11-dev linux package (load it)
- an environment variable MEFISTO=DirMefisto/mefisto not initialized
- an environment variable MEFISTOX=$HOME/mefistox not initialized
- a directory DirMefisto/bin   without shell-scripts INITIER MAILLER ... to reload


INSTALLATION OF A USER OF MEFISTO:
==================================
instalsource.bash modifies the  personal file .bashrc in $HOME directory
by addition of the 2 environment variables

export MEFISTO=DirMefisto/mefisto
export MEFISTOX=$HOME/mefistox

and after the definition of PATH and before the command export PATH, add
export PATH=.:$PATH:$MEFISTO/bin
export CDPATH=.:$HOME:$MEFISTO:$MEFISTOX

Then, under Linux, the typing of commands INITIER, MAILLER, ELASTICER, FLUIDER,
NLSER, THERMICER, cbl_tout, ...  will be found.
                   
REMARK on X11 WINDOWS SYSTEM:
=============================
Mefisto necessitates an installed libX11-dev package at different levels
- at compilation of the C subroutines
- at execution to draw the results
If your system does not contain it, it is necessary to load libX11-dev package
of your linux distribution.

In a same way, the package ImageMagick must be installed in order the call of
the command "convert" permits the construction of an animated gif file to
visualize the solution.

